    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about" class="container content-section" style="padding-top: 70px">
        <h2 class="text-center">What is Planktos?</h2>
        <p class="text-center">Planktos enables websites to serve their static content peer-to-peer by having users serve static assets to other users. This allows website owners to significantly reduce hosting costs for static content, scale in real-time without provisioning more web servers, and prevent user impact during an outage. Integrating Planktos into an existing website is as easy as running the command line tool on your static files.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- How It Works Section -->
    <section class="container content-section" style="padding-top: 50px">
        <div class="center-block" style="width:75%">
            <h2 class="text-center">How it works</h2>
            <p class="text-center">
                <b>1.</b> Planktos bundles your website's static files into a torrent<br/>
                <b>2.</b> HTTP requests are intercepted by the Planktos service worker<br/>
                <b>3.</b> Requested files are downloaded from other online users via BitTorrent<br/>
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Benefits section -->
    <section id="benefits" class="container content-section" style="padding-top: 75px">
        <h2 class="text-center">Benefits of using Planktos</h2>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-users" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    peer-to-peer
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Planktos uses <a target="_blank" href="https://webtorrent.io">WebTorrent</a> to convert users of your website into seeders, enabling them to serve static content to other users. This reduces server bandwidth and makes your website more resilient.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-code" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Simple &amp; Easy Integration
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Using Planktos is as simple as including the Planktos install script and using the Planktos command line interface to bundle your website's static files into a torrent.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-life-ring" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Avoid downtime
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Planktos can serve your website even if your web servers go down. Any users that visited your website prior to an outage will still be able to access it.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-bolt" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Auto Scaling
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Since Planktos turns users of your website into seeders, any increase in demand is also an increase in supply; with more users, downloads get faster.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-wrench" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Customizable
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Planktos has sensible defaults and a simple interface for customization, allowing you to tweak it to your needs.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-chrome" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Supports top browsers
                    <i class="fa fa-firefox" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Planktos supports Chrome and Firefox with no plugins needed. When Planktos encounters an unsupported browser it gracefully falls back to default settings.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-lock" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Secure
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                  All files downloaded from peers are cryptographically verified as required by the BitTorrent specification.
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-5 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-files-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Supports all file types
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                  Whether it's HTML, CSS, Javascript, images, videos, or something else it all works with Planktos.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 text-center" style="padding-bottom: 45px">
                <h4>
                    <i class="fa fa-archive" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    Improved Caching
                </h4>
                <div style="font-size: medium">
                    Once files are downloaded, they are persisted to disk and used for any subsequent requests. Since Planktos stores file hashes, there is no need for the browser to ask your web server if any files have changed.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

